positively affected by full compliance with a periodontal maintenance program in 
a specialist practice.
CONCLUSIONS: Within the limits of this study, data suggest that tooth retention 
and clinical improvements following GTR treatment of intrabony defects can be 
maintained long term in the great majority of cases and thus that regenerative 
periodontal treatment represents an important alternative for the management of 
severely compromised teeth.

